The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Boy suicide after scolding
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      Boy suicide after scolding
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	A Class XI student of a school in Dunlop was found hanging in his Cossipore home on Thursday, a day after his parents had allegedly scolded him for neglecting his studies.         
	Neighbours said Sagar Mondal, 18, had played carom with friends till 10pm on Wednesday. His parents scolded him as his exams were five days away. At 8am on Thursday, Sagars parents  Madhusudan, who works in a cinema hall, and Shyamali  went out.         
	His mother returned to find him hanging at 8.25am, said a neighbour.                                                                                                                                                           
